1
00:00:00,458 --> 00:00:03,128
(Previously) Didn't you say you wanted to
act in something I direct?

2
00:00:03,211 --> 00:00:04,796
Why did you include Raffy in this project?

3
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:06,089
Was there really no one else?

4
00:00:06,172 --> 00:00:07,674
Why? Scared of losing?

5
00:00:08,133 --> 00:00:09,175
I never lose.

6
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:10,135
How about this, Rome?

7
00:00:10,343 --> 00:00:11,344
Let me serve him up for you.

8
00:00:11,386 --> 00:00:13,596
Whether you take him or not, that's your call.

9
00:00:14,597 --> 00:00:17,100
If we do it one more time, will you tell Jack?

10
00:00:17,392 --> 00:00:18,101
Why would I?

11
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:19,477
Something this delicious…

12
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:21,646
I'd rather keep to myself.

13
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:25,316
Nice move.
Sneaking your crush into the project.

14
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:29,154
If you like him that much,
you should try kissing him.

15
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:32,115
Am I too late?

16
00:00:34,075 --> 00:00:36,036
Guys, this is my friend Boston.

17
00:00:36,202 --> 00:00:37,454
Mind if I join your friend group?

18
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,500
(Episode 3: Memory Recall)

19
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,100
(A Year Ago)

20
00:00:46,254 --> 00:00:46,921
Tua.

21
00:00:47,505 --> 00:00:48,506
Check that guy out.

22
00:00:48,923 --> 00:00:49,841
He's a looker.

23
00:00:51,176 --> 00:00:51,926
Damn.

24
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:53,511
Is this place always this wild?

25
00:00:53,678 --> 00:00:54,721
It always is.

26
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:58,933
If you want to have fun tonight,
don't hold back.

27
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:01,186
Come on, Tua. Come!

28
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:08,151
Dean.

29
00:01:14,866 --> 00:01:15,867
What took you so long?

30
00:01:17,118 --> 00:01:18,536
I had to drag Tua here.

31
00:01:18,703 --> 00:01:20,413
He's drunk and whining about going home.

32
00:01:21,456 --> 00:01:22,832
This is my friend Boston.

33
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:25,126
We studied Business Management together
before I transferred here.

34
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:26,961
This is Dean, my boyfriend.

35
00:01:27,128 --> 00:01:29,089
And that's Tua,
a friend from the same faculty.

36
00:01:31,925 --> 00:01:32,801
You've got good taste.

37
00:01:34,344 --> 00:01:34,969
Of course.

38
00:01:37,013 --> 00:01:37,847
What about you, Tua?

39
00:01:38,681 --> 00:01:39,724
Why didn't you bring your partner?

40
00:01:40,975 --> 00:01:42,143
He doesn't have one.

41
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:43,812
Help him find one.

42
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:45,522
Don't.

43
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:49,734
Hey, I'll go get us some drinks.

44
00:01:50,235 --> 00:01:51,027
Come with me.
Sure.

45
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:00,870
Go all in tonight.

46
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:02,497
I'll take care of you.

47
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:36,573
Hey.

48
00:02:37,115 --> 00:02:38,032
Keep this pose.

49
00:02:39,617 --> 00:02:40,076
Why?

50
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:43,580
Let me take a photo of you.

51
00:02:45,248 --> 00:02:45,999
Why?

52
00:02:47,709 --> 00:02:49,544
I like capturing moments after sex.

53
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:54,799
Do you take photos
of everyone you sleep with?

54
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,720
Not everyone.

55
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:03,850
Only some who are special to me.

56
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:17,030
Here we go.

57
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:35,500
"Only Friends : Dream On"

58
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:08,474
Okay.

59
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:10,685
Remember, this is your mark.

60
00:05:13,938 --> 00:05:14,856
Let me check your shirt.

61
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:17,942
Ready?

62
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:21,529
One, two, three.

63
00:05:26,868 --> 00:05:27,285
Here you go.

64
00:05:35,168 --> 00:05:37,879
Tua, are you okay seeing your first again?

65
00:05:39,464 --> 00:05:40,631
You don't have to rub it in.

66
00:05:43,885 --> 00:05:46,679
Poor you. Your first had to be
the most notorious one out there.

67
00:05:47,930 --> 00:05:48,639
Yes, he is.

68
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:51,392
And you're the one who
dragged me to see him that night.

69
00:05:51,684 --> 00:05:52,727
So that's my fault?

70
00:05:52,977 --> 00:05:54,354
You left with him on your own.

71
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:55,813
I didn't force you. Right?

72
00:05:56,981 --> 00:05:58,441
Yeah. Just forget it.

73
00:05:58,816 --> 00:06:01,611
I'll take that as material to grow from.

74
00:06:02,278 --> 00:06:04,072
Art never comes from happiness anyway.

75
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:05,615
Okay, okay.

76
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:07,742
Hey.

77
00:06:08,117 --> 00:06:11,871
If you want to erase someone from the past,
you need someone new.

78
00:06:13,956 --> 00:06:16,292
Here he comes. Your someone new.

79
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:21,714
So, how was the kiss?

80
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:25,259
I haven't had the guts to talk to him yet.

81
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:29,931
Then talk to him. Go on.

82
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:31,182
Trust me.

83
00:06:31,599 --> 00:06:32,225
Bye now.

84
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:34,811
See you upstairs, Arnold.

85
00:06:36,187 --> 00:06:36,437
Tua.

86
00:06:36,938 --> 00:06:38,022
What's the next outfit?

87
00:06:39,357 --> 00:06:40,066
I'll grab it for you.

88
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:50,743
Let me help.

89
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:01,629
Hey.
Hm?

90
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:05,258
I want to talk about that kiss.

91
00:07:06,801 --> 00:07:08,845
You should know, that night I…

92
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:09,679
Oh, come on.

93
00:07:10,471 --> 00:07:11,347
It's totally fine.

94
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:12,390
No problem at all.

95
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:15,601
You were drunk. I was drunk too.

96
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:16,853
Don't overthink it.

97
00:07:17,228 --> 00:07:18,187
I'm not thinking about it either.

98
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:22,859
Yeah. I'm not overthinking it.

99
00:07:23,317 --> 00:07:24,235
I just wanted to tease you.

100
00:07:24,986 --> 00:07:28,656
Now that we've kissed,
your love scenes should be easier.

101
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:34,704
Change your pants.

102
00:07:58,311 --> 00:07:59,896
You somehow managed to
sneak into this project.

103
00:08:01,939 --> 00:08:02,899
What could I do?

104
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:04,650
Jack asked me.

105
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:11,657
Did he? Or did he just feel sorry for you?

106
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:14,827
At least that's better than
sleeping your way into a role.

107
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:16,287
What's that called?

108
00:08:19,123 --> 00:08:24,462
That's called ex-boyfriends
who are still in love and still hooking up.

109
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:30,510
Come on.

110
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:32,762
Get to the set. Go.

111
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,023
Poor thing.

112
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:48,903
You confessed to Jack,
but he turned you down.

113
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:53,449
You decided to audition,
and all you got was a supporting role.

114
00:08:58,955 --> 00:09:00,206
Just don't fall.

115
00:09:00,581 --> 00:09:01,666
Or I will step right on you.

116
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:06,045
Someone like you can't touch me.

117
00:09:07,755 --> 00:09:08,339
Ready?

118
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:10,299
Get to your mark.

119
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:13,052
Right here?

120
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:15,346
Yeah. Get ready to shoot.

121
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:26,107
Hey.

122
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:28,943
I'm heading out. In a rush.

123
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,153
Aren't you going to eat?

124
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:33,656
No. I need to
open a bank account for the play.

125
00:09:34,198 --> 00:09:34,865
See you. Bye.

126
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:48,671
What's wrong? You can't eat that?

127
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:56,679
I don't like seafood.
It sometimes gives me a rash.

128
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:00,766
Then take this.

129
00:10:03,894 --> 00:10:05,104
Mine is chicken and garlic.

130
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:06,981
You can eat chicken, right?

131
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,571
It's fine. I can order something.
You eat your food.

132
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:15,698
Oh, just eat. Here.

133
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:18,826
People don't know you're allergic to seafood.

134
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,912
If you order something else,
they might think badly of you.

135
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:26,959
Is there some subtext here?

136
00:10:28,586 --> 00:10:29,879
Subtext, my ass.

137
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:31,130
It's just food.

138
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:32,798
You've been watching too many dramas?

139
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:52,985
Hey.

140
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:56,739
Should we go swimming after this?

141
00:10:57,198 --> 00:10:58,324
I want to work out.

142
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:02,119
Don't read too much into it

143
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:03,788
Our one-night...

144
00:11:05,373 --> 00:11:09,377
No. Our two-night stand stays between us.

145
00:11:14,382 --> 00:11:16,092
Oh, please.

146
00:11:16,217 --> 00:11:17,551
I'm just trying to be friends.

147
00:11:17,968 --> 00:11:20,554
Just because we hooked up
doesn't mean we can't be friends.

148
00:11:21,597 --> 00:11:22,056
So?

149
00:11:22,264 --> 00:11:23,182
How about that swim?

150
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:26,686
Let me check my mood first.

151
00:11:27,228 --> 00:11:28,604
I'll give you an answer after the shoot.

152
00:11:32,608 --> 00:11:33,150
Water.

153
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:04,140
Why did you bring Boston in
to work with you?

154
00:12:07,059 --> 00:12:07,810
Why?

155
00:12:08,477 --> 00:12:09,687
I just asked him to help out.

156
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:12,648
And did you know that…

157
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:18,279
the guy helping you out
nailed and bailed on Tua?

158
00:12:22,324 --> 00:12:23,492
Are you serious?

159
00:12:23,868 --> 00:12:24,618
Dead serious.

160
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:32,334
Tell Boston he can be on his way
after this shoot.

161
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:35,379
I can't.

162
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:40,801
I told him he'd be doing behind-the-scenes
photos until the project ends.

163
00:12:41,218 --> 00:12:42,052
Then cancel him.

164
00:12:43,637 --> 00:12:45,181
I gave him my word.

165
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:50,561
Besides, you know
we don't have any sponsors yet.

166
00:12:52,563 --> 00:12:55,107
It's good to have his support.
It saves us money.

167
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:02,156
How about this? You keep an eye on Tua.

168
00:13:02,364 --> 00:13:04,617
And I'll keep an eye on Boston.

169
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:06,660
I'll keep him at arm's length.

170
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:10,498
Okay then.

171
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:12,958
Just watch him.

172
00:13:16,295 --> 00:13:16,879
Yeah.

173
00:13:23,928 --> 00:13:25,262
One more thing.

174
00:13:27,556 --> 00:13:30,309
I'm coming over today.

175
00:13:34,897 --> 00:13:35,731
What for?

176
00:13:37,566 --> 00:13:38,359
Well…

177
00:13:40,277 --> 00:13:41,779
I left my wallet there that night.

178
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:45,616
No need.

179
00:13:46,408 --> 00:13:47,409
I'll bring it to you.

180
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:50,830
Your guard's really up.

181
00:13:51,705 --> 00:13:55,084
What is this? A nail-and-bail on me, too?

182
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:00,339
You're just like your friend.

183
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:15,271
All the outfits look great.

184
00:14:16,772 --> 00:14:17,106
Mm.

185
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:26,156
Still mad about before?

186
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:30,494
No.

187
00:14:31,579 --> 00:14:32,663
Why would I be?

188
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:36,500
Not mad, but it's still on your mind, yeah?

189
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:41,338
It's never easy to forget our first.

190
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:43,757
Especially when they set the bar high.

191
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:51,432
Who said you set the bar high?

192
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:55,352
There are plenty of people better than you.

193
00:14:56,562 --> 00:14:57,938
Does that mean
you're seeing someone new?

194
00:15:03,235 --> 00:15:04,153
Do I have to answer that?

195
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,252
Come on.

196
00:15:22,546 --> 00:15:24,006
Let's just leave the past behind.

197
00:15:25,215 --> 00:15:26,550
I want to start over.

198
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:29,929
It'd be nice to start over with you.

199
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:37,561
You don't have to answer me right now.

200
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:39,521
I just want you to know…

201
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:44,151
that I'm courting you.

202
00:16:00,584 --> 00:16:01,794
I am back.

203
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:12,596
What are you looking at?

204
00:16:13,889 --> 00:16:15,057
At someone so easy to fool.

205
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:17,893
One box of food
and you're already here with me.

206
00:16:19,478 --> 00:16:20,270
I can just leave now.
Hey!

207
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:22,398
I'm kidding.

208
00:16:23,565 --> 00:16:25,359
You get worked up so easily.

209
00:16:27,319 --> 00:16:27,903
Hey, Rome.

210
00:16:27,903 --> 00:16:28,988
Hi, Bas.

211
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:30,072
Hi.

212
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:31,949
I rarely see you.

213
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:34,785
It's hard to book you for a party these days.

214
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:37,746
Come on, bro. It's my final year.

215
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:39,665
The workload's a bit heavy.

216
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:44,461
But tonight, the client
specifically asked for you, Rome.

217
00:16:44,795 --> 00:16:45,754
Don't bail on me.

218
00:16:45,838 --> 00:16:48,173
Of course not. A deal's a deal.

219
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:49,216
I'll see you then.

220
00:16:49,466 --> 00:16:49,925
Sure.

221
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:55,222
Hold on, the client
asked for someone else too.

222
00:16:56,473 --> 00:16:58,475
What's his name again?

223
00:16:58,642 --> 00:16:59,476
Your friend…

224
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:02,479
James Dean?

225
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:06,191
Where's he working now? He just vanished.

226
00:17:06,608 --> 00:17:08,110
Lots of my clients ask about him.

227
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:11,655
I don't know, bro. I can't remember.

228
00:17:13,198 --> 00:17:14,491
What a shame.

229
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:17,953
If you see him, tell him to come back.

230
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:19,747
He's always welcome.

231
00:17:21,498 --> 00:17:22,249
Of course.

232
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:23,167
Okay.

233
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:24,460
I'll see you tonight.

234
00:17:24,626 --> 00:17:25,169
See you.

235
00:17:31,842 --> 00:17:32,301
Let's go.

236
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:13,175
What's up with you?

237
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:20,057
What are you doing?

238
00:18:21,016 --> 00:18:22,684
This is a public place.

239
00:18:26,146 --> 00:18:28,607
Isn't that your thing? Doing it outdoors.

240
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:43,789
So you work as a host or something?

241
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:45,833
No.

242
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:48,043
I don't do that kind of work.

243
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:54,424
Then, who was that James Dean
you used to work with?

244
00:18:57,094 --> 00:18:58,929
I don't know. I don't remember.

245
00:18:59,888 --> 00:19:03,517
I'm just a DJ at rich people's birthday parties.

246
00:19:06,186 --> 00:19:06,812
Ah.

247
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:14,570
You're working tonight?

248
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:16,989
Mm.

249
00:19:29,877 --> 00:19:31,295
Can I tag along?

250
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:33,213
No.
It's work.

251
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:42,556
Hey.

252
00:19:43,765 --> 00:19:44,308
Why did you stop?

253
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:46,685
If you don't take me with you,
I'm not continuing.

254
00:19:47,561 --> 00:19:48,187
Come on.

255
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:49,897
Can't you at least get me off first?

256
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:50,981
No.

257
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:03,410
Fine, you can come.

258
00:20:03,702 --> 00:20:05,454
But there are tons of secrets at this party.

259
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:08,665
Whatever you see, keep it to yourself.

260
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,233
Wow.

261
00:20:34,691 --> 00:20:36,193
We barely made it before the rain.

262
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:37,110
Right.

263
00:20:37,402 --> 00:20:39,238
I rode as fast as I could.

264
00:20:43,825 --> 00:20:45,619
Hey, Tua.

265
00:20:46,286 --> 00:20:47,829
You've got more stuff?

266
00:20:49,164 --> 00:20:52,292
Just in case I need them for future projects.

267
00:21:01,593 --> 00:21:02,761
What's wrong, Tua?

268
00:21:03,053 --> 00:21:05,430
You've looked uneasy since the studio.

269
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:07,474
It's…

270
00:21:09,351 --> 00:21:11,728
It's nothing. I'm just tired.

271
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:13,730
Are you sure?

272
00:21:20,654 --> 00:21:22,614
I shouldn't have asked you to take me home.

273
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:24,241
Sorry for the hassle.

274
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:25,784
What hassle, Tua?

275
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:26,910
It's fine.

276
00:21:28,745 --> 00:21:33,458
But it's pouring.
I don't think I can leave anytime soon.

277
00:21:37,421 --> 00:21:39,548
You can crash here.

278
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:41,133
Wait until the rain lets up.

279
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:43,552
Can I really?

280
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:45,429
I don't want to bother Dean.

281
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:47,097
Oh, come on.

282
00:21:47,097 --> 00:21:48,932
Dean's hardly ever here.

283
00:21:49,266 --> 00:21:49,975
Don't worry about it.

284
00:21:52,352 --> 00:21:53,562
Mm. Okay.

285
00:21:54,771 --> 00:21:56,773
Then I'll take your offer.

286
00:21:57,274 --> 00:21:57,607
Mm.

287
00:21:57,607 --> 00:21:58,817
I'll just go take a shower.

288
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:00,527
I feel sticky all over.

289
00:22:03,947 --> 00:22:06,366
I'll grab you a towel.

290
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:07,576
Thank you.

291
00:22:18,378 --> 00:22:19,504
So, how was New York?

292
00:22:20,130 --> 00:22:21,173
Had fun with all your one-night stands?

293
00:22:21,465 --> 00:22:23,342
Wow, it was fucking amazing.

294
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:26,219
Everyone can just be themselves.

295
00:22:26,303 --> 00:22:28,472
They do whatever they want,
get laid with whoever they like.

296
00:22:29,389 --> 00:22:30,557
Then why did you come back?

297
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:32,684
I didn't think you'd return to Thailand.

298
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:38,523
Honestly, it was fun at first.

299
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:41,860
But after a while, I found it hard.

300
00:22:42,152 --> 00:22:43,320
It's more comfortable here.

301
00:22:44,988 --> 00:22:46,448
But I think you'd love it there.

302
00:22:46,823 --> 00:22:48,408
You can watch
Broadway shows all year round.

303
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:50,494
Mm.

304
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:53,455
I'd love to visit too.

305
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:02,714
So, are you back with Dean?

306
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:05,092
No.

307
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:07,552
We're just working on the play together.

308
00:23:08,303 --> 00:23:08,887
Seriously?

309
00:23:10,013 --> 00:23:11,348
I don't think it's just that.

310
00:23:13,392 --> 00:23:16,228
Can someone like you work with your ex?

311
00:23:17,562 --> 00:23:18,730
I know my boundaries.

312
00:23:20,065 --> 00:23:20,399
Okay.

313
00:23:26,863 --> 00:23:28,698
Wow. Speak of the devil.

314
00:23:49,219 --> 00:23:50,470
(Did you change the door passcode?)

315
00:23:51,471 --> 00:23:52,931
That's none of your concern.

316
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:54,724
(This is how you want to play it, Jack?)

317
00:23:55,016 --> 00:23:56,852
I'll hang up now. I'm busy.

318
00:24:01,064 --> 00:24:03,733
He's still blowing up your phone.
Clearly, he's not letting go.

319
00:24:04,025 --> 00:24:04,568
Go set things straight.

320
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:13,535
Sir, I can't reach my partner.

321
00:24:13,994 --> 00:24:15,245
Could you please open his room for me?

322
00:24:15,829 --> 00:24:16,705
I can't.

323
00:24:16,705 --> 00:24:18,206
Only the resident can open the door.

324
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:22,002
But I can't wait anymore.

325
00:24:23,170 --> 00:24:24,588
He's been so stressed lately.

326
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:26,465
He hasn't been sleeping,
and he's been saying weird things.

327
00:24:26,965 --> 00:24:27,924
I'm scared, sir.

328
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:30,177
I'm afraid he might do something bad.

329
00:24:31,136 --> 00:24:31,636
I can't.

330
00:24:32,846 --> 00:24:34,723
Please, sir. Please help me.

331
00:24:34,723 --> 00:24:36,433
If he dies, what am I gonna do?

332
00:24:36,433 --> 00:24:39,269
He could be dying up there right now.
Please help.

333
00:24:43,648 --> 00:24:44,483
I'll wait here.
Talk things out calmly, okay?

334
00:24:45,484 --> 00:24:46,359
Sure. Thank you.

335
00:24:55,452 --> 00:24:57,913
He's just drunk and sleeping.

336
00:24:58,580 --> 00:24:59,539
There's nothing to worry about.

337
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:02,542
Thank you for your help. I'll take it from here.

338
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:03,710
Are you sure?

339
00:25:04,586 --> 00:25:06,254
Should I call an ambulance or the police?

340
00:25:06,630 --> 00:25:07,422
No, sir.

341
00:25:07,672 --> 00:25:08,381
Thank you so much.

342
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,691
How did you get into my room?

343
00:26:51,234 --> 00:26:52,694
Why can't I get in?

344
00:26:55,322 --> 00:26:57,032
Are you hiding something from me?

345
00:26:58,325 --> 00:26:59,576
What would I be hiding?

346
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:10,378
So what is this?

347
00:27:13,048 --> 00:27:14,090
None of your business.

348
00:27:18,887 --> 00:27:20,430
When did you go to rehab?

349
00:27:20,639 --> 00:27:22,557
Why didn't I know about it?

350
00:27:24,893 --> 00:27:26,478
Are you an alcoholic, Jack?

351
00:27:30,607 --> 00:27:32,150
Why do you care?

352
00:27:37,614 --> 00:27:39,240
Why didn't you take care of yourself?

353
00:27:39,282 --> 00:27:40,950
How did you let this happen?

354
00:27:43,620 --> 00:27:46,581
I ended up in rehab because of you.

355
00:27:49,709 --> 00:27:51,378
But I'm fine now.

356
00:27:52,003 --> 00:27:53,672
I'm clean.

357
00:27:58,802 --> 00:28:00,762
Why didn't you ever tell me?

358
00:28:01,888 --> 00:28:05,517
Doesn't what I'm doing these days
make up for what I did?

359
00:28:06,309 --> 00:28:09,270
Are you really going to stay mad at me
for the same thing forever?

360
00:28:10,146 --> 00:28:14,109
I swear, it was just work.

361
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:16,069
Nothing else happened.

362
00:28:16,403 --> 00:28:17,278
It's fine, Dean.

363
00:28:18,363 --> 00:28:19,781
Because no matter what you say,

364
00:28:21,282 --> 00:28:23,034
I'm not putting myself
in the same spot again.

365
00:28:23,493 --> 00:28:24,160
Therefore…

366
00:28:24,869 --> 00:28:25,995
Leave.

367
00:28:32,335 --> 00:28:33,461
I'm not leaving.

368
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:35,088
I said leave.

369
00:28:35,338 --> 00:28:36,089
I'm not leaving.

370
00:28:36,631 --> 00:28:37,841
I said leave.

371
00:28:37,924 --> 00:28:38,883
I'm not leaving!

372
00:28:39,634 --> 00:28:40,343
You're not?
No.

373
00:28:41,636 --> 00:28:42,679
Hey, Jack!

374
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:45,390
Jack, you asshole. Let me go!

375
00:28:46,808 --> 00:28:47,058
Jack!
- Go!
- Ouch!

376
00:28:49,310 --> 00:28:49,853
Ouch.

377
00:28:51,688 --> 00:28:52,230
Jack!

378
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:54,524
Hey!

379
00:29:00,655 --> 00:29:01,239
It's in the past.

380
00:29:03,032 --> 00:29:03,908
I don't want to remember.

381
00:29:17,630 --> 00:29:18,173
Here.

382
00:29:28,475 --> 00:29:30,226
Did Dean forget his key?

383
00:29:30,518 --> 00:29:32,604
I'll get it. You keep watching.

384
00:29:32,729 --> 00:29:33,396
Mm.

385
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:52,123
Why are you here?

386
00:29:52,540 --> 00:29:53,750
To see you.

387
00:29:56,544 --> 00:29:57,670
Hey, Boston.

388
00:29:59,088 --> 00:30:00,381
Hey, Arnold.

389
00:30:02,091 --> 00:30:03,426
What are you guys up to?

390
00:30:03,593 --> 00:30:04,427
Watching a movie.

391
00:30:05,887 --> 00:30:08,306
Looks interesting. Mind if I join?

392
00:30:08,848 --> 00:30:11,267
Of course. The more the merrier.

393
00:30:16,815 --> 00:30:18,900
Tua, why are you just standing there?

394
00:30:33,164 --> 00:30:34,290
Oh, hey, Arnold.

395
00:30:34,833 --> 00:30:36,459
I forgot to tell you back on set.

396
00:30:36,543 --> 00:30:37,877
You have a great body.

397
00:30:38,336 --> 00:30:40,171
And those Romeo outfits suit you.

398
00:30:41,172 --> 00:30:42,549
Tua's the real talent.

399
00:30:43,049 --> 00:30:44,425
He makes amazing costumes.

400
00:30:49,472 --> 00:30:53,268
You give off the same vibe as
the models I photographed in New York.

401
00:30:53,977 --> 00:30:54,644
Me?

402
00:30:54,936 --> 00:30:55,854
Yes, really.

403
00:30:56,479 --> 00:30:59,732
With your looks, with a little practice,
you could audition to walk the runway.

404
00:31:03,778 --> 00:31:05,905
What was your job like?

405
00:31:06,656 --> 00:31:07,448
My job?

406
00:31:12,912 --> 00:31:14,497
Something like this.

407
00:31:15,039 --> 00:31:16,457
People hire me to shoot their profile photos

408
00:31:16,457 --> 00:31:19,002
so they can send them to
high-end or streetwear brands.

409
00:31:21,379 --> 00:31:23,047
Boston, you take really good photos.

410
00:31:26,885 --> 00:31:28,219
Why don't you model for me?

411
00:31:29,679 --> 00:31:30,388
Me?

412
00:31:32,473 --> 00:31:32,974
All right.

413
00:31:34,684 --> 00:31:35,602
You'd be perfect.

414
00:31:37,353 --> 00:31:38,563
I'll go get more snacks.

415
00:31:45,236 --> 00:31:46,529
Can you grab me a beer too?

416
00:31:56,289 --> 00:32:01,544
Honestly, Boston is the last person
I want Arnold to associate with.

417
00:32:15,058 --> 00:32:17,602
So this is your side gig?

418
00:32:18,353 --> 00:32:19,646
Why do you do it?

419
00:32:19,979 --> 00:32:21,397
You don't look like you need the money.

420
00:32:21,648 --> 00:32:23,024
I'm not doing it for the money.

421
00:32:23,149 --> 00:32:24,233
I just want the experience.

422
00:32:24,901 --> 00:32:25,735
For what?

423
00:32:25,985 --> 00:32:27,236
So you can become some big DJ?

424
00:32:27,654 --> 00:32:28,905
Playing in huge clubs?

425
00:32:29,364 --> 00:32:30,156
No.

426
00:32:30,448 --> 00:32:31,741
I want to DJ at festivals.

427
00:32:32,367 --> 00:32:34,202
One day, I'll play at Tomorrowland.

428
00:32:34,494 --> 00:32:37,288
Whoa. You dream big.

429
00:32:38,539 --> 00:32:41,751
If you make it, I'll buy a ticket.

430
00:32:44,379 --> 00:32:48,341
You'd better start saving now. Because I will.

431
00:32:52,178 --> 00:32:53,888
You're kind of like Jack.

432
00:32:55,390 --> 00:32:58,726
Is ambition in both of your DNA?

433
00:32:59,185 --> 00:33:00,645
What the hell are you talking about?

434
00:33:00,895 --> 00:33:02,355
I don't share his DNA.

435
00:33:02,730 --> 00:33:04,190
Don't compare me to him.

436
00:33:07,193 --> 00:33:08,611
Hey, dude!

437
00:33:08,987 --> 00:33:10,446
Hi, Bas.

438
00:33:11,447 --> 00:33:13,992
What's up, man? Haven't seen you in ages.

439
00:33:14,325 --> 00:33:16,369
Why are you sitting here? Already drunk?

440
00:33:16,577 --> 00:33:18,496
My hosts are all great, you know?

441
00:33:18,496 --> 00:33:19,539
Sure thing. They're incredible.

442
00:33:19,580 --> 00:33:20,456
Hey, I'll be right back.
Okay.

443
00:33:27,046 --> 00:33:28,214
I'm stepping out for a smoke.

444
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:29,173
Yeah.

445
00:33:31,884 --> 00:33:32,969
Hi, Bas.

446
00:33:34,804 --> 00:33:35,471
Hey.

447
00:33:36,389 --> 00:33:37,807
Rome brought you here?

448
00:33:41,310 --> 00:33:42,729
Are you two really friends?

449
00:33:42,895 --> 00:33:44,313
Of course, we are.

450
00:33:45,773 --> 00:33:48,776
By the way,
If I'm interested in this kind of work,

451
00:33:49,902 --> 00:33:51,070
could I join your team?

452
00:33:53,072 --> 00:33:53,781
Sure.

453
00:33:54,991 --> 00:33:58,327
If you're serious, you can even start tonight.

454
00:34:00,371 --> 00:34:03,332
Would I get the same rate as James Dean?

455
00:34:11,007 --> 00:34:12,717
You're friends with James Dean?

456
00:34:16,179 --> 00:34:18,139
I'm not sure if
we're talking about the same Dean.

457
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:21,768
But if we are, I could
bring him back to work for you.

458
00:34:22,143 --> 00:34:23,186
We're friends.

459
00:34:23,436 --> 00:34:24,937
We can come to work together.

460
00:34:25,605 --> 00:34:28,566
Do you have a photo of him, though?

461
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:31,778
I do.

462
00:34:35,865 --> 00:34:39,577
Actually, he only started last year.

463
00:34:40,328 --> 00:34:41,746
Not hosting like this, though.

464
00:34:42,663 --> 00:34:45,625
He mostly just entertained
some clients over meals.

465
00:34:49,462 --> 00:34:49,837
Mm.

466
00:34:52,465 --> 00:34:52,924
Here.

467
00:35:00,056 --> 00:35:01,224
Hey, Bas. Come here.

468
00:35:01,516 --> 00:35:02,809
The birthday boy is blowing out the candles.

469
00:35:02,809 --> 00:35:03,976
Alright, alright.

470
00:35:04,936 --> 00:35:06,104
Hold on.

471
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:07,814
Add my contact.

472
00:35:07,939 --> 00:35:09,440
You can send me your comp card later.

473
00:35:09,941 --> 00:35:11,442
I'm coming!

474
00:35:11,818 --> 00:35:13,319
Whoo-hoo!

475
00:35:19,075 --> 00:35:20,201
FRIEND SEARCH

476
00:35:21,160 --> 00:35:22,161
ADD

477
00:35:28,709 --> 00:35:30,419
UNSEND THIS MESSAGE?

478
00:35:30,419 --> 00:35:32,505
UNSEND

479
00:35:51,023 --> 00:35:52,942
Alright, everyone. Are we ready?

480
00:35:52,942 --> 00:35:55,319
Let's begin our first read-through
of Romeo & Romeo.

481
00:35:55,736 --> 00:35:56,988
Take out your scripts.

482
00:36:03,411 --> 00:36:04,412
Let's start.

483
00:36:10,459 --> 00:36:12,128
Everybody, please mute your phones.

484
00:36:12,545 --> 00:36:13,963
This won't take long.

485
00:36:13,963 --> 00:36:16,424
Once we're done, we can get back to work.

486
00:36:41,365 --> 00:36:42,033
Dean.

487
00:36:42,366 --> 00:36:43,034
Hmm?

488
00:37:06,682 --> 00:37:09,685
Jack, I think we should call it a day.

489
00:37:27,912 --> 00:37:28,913
Alright, guys.

490
00:37:28,913 --> 00:37:30,039
We'll stop here for today.

491
00:37:30,164 --> 00:37:31,457
I'll reschedule the meeting.

492
00:37:31,457 --> 00:37:31,999
Sorry.
Go on.

493
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:34,627
I'm sorry.

494
00:37:35,503 --> 00:37:37,838
Thank you for today. You're all free to go.

495
00:37:40,049 --> 00:37:42,718
Can you wait outside? We'll talk later.

496
00:37:52,895 --> 00:37:54,313
Who the hell did this?

497
00:37:55,481 --> 00:37:57,525
Isn't it just the four of us who know?

498
00:37:59,568 --> 00:38:01,570
Did you tell someone
when you were drunk, Dean?

499
00:38:02,029 --> 00:38:03,364
I never told anyone.

500
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:07,535
They sent it to the faculty group chat,
using a fake account.

501
00:38:08,327 --> 00:38:09,996
Someone's targeting you.

502
00:38:15,167 --> 00:38:16,877
Be honest with me, Jack.

503
00:38:16,919 --> 00:38:19,463
You didn't spread this
because you were mad at me, did you?

504
00:38:22,341 --> 00:38:24,010
What the fuck are you saying?

505
00:38:24,176 --> 00:38:25,720
You hated my job.

506
00:38:25,886 --> 00:38:27,013
Damn right I did.

507
00:38:27,847 --> 00:38:28,973
But I could accept that.

508
00:38:30,766 --> 00:38:32,810
What I couldn't accept was you lying to me.

509
00:38:34,312 --> 00:38:36,689
Guys, it was a long time ago.

510
00:38:37,148 --> 00:38:38,524
Can you drop it?

511
00:38:38,524 --> 00:38:39,900
Why should I, Timmy?

512
00:38:40,818 --> 00:38:42,236
He did lie to me.

513
00:38:43,696 --> 00:38:46,949
He told me he'd stop
taking jobs from that guy.

514
00:38:48,075 --> 00:38:49,035
But you…

515
00:38:50,911 --> 00:38:53,205
kept contacting him behind my back.

516
00:38:53,956 --> 00:38:56,375
I told you I still had financial problems.

517
00:38:56,709 --> 00:38:58,210
I didn't have the same choices you did, Jack.

518
00:38:58,210 --> 00:38:59,378
What an excuse.

519
00:38:59,420 --> 00:39:00,796
Everybody has a choice.

520
00:39:01,255 --> 00:39:02,423
You just chose to do it.

521
00:39:02,423 --> 00:39:03,507
Easy for you to say.

522
00:39:04,425 --> 00:39:06,010
You didn't have it as tough as I did.

523
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:07,678
You've never had to struggle like I did!

524
00:39:07,678 --> 00:39:08,888
That's not the point, Dean!

525
00:39:10,681 --> 00:39:12,892
You must accept the choice you made.

526
00:39:14,685 --> 00:39:18,147
And you don't have the right
to doubt me or get mad at me!

527
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:19,315
Jack, you bastard!

528
00:39:19,648 --> 00:39:20,274
What?

529
00:39:20,483 --> 00:39:21,275
You fucking asshole!

530
00:39:21,776 --> 00:39:22,610
It's the truth!
Hey!

531
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:24,236
Enough!

532
00:39:24,528 --> 00:39:25,780
Pull your shit together!

533
00:39:26,822 --> 00:39:28,199
Why would Jack do it?

534
00:39:28,574 --> 00:39:31,786
Stop fighting and find the one who did it.

535
00:39:32,119 --> 00:39:32,703
Screw this.

536
00:39:37,958 --> 00:39:40,002
Everyone's already judged me.

537
00:39:43,255 --> 00:39:44,799
Nobody cares anyway.

538
00:39:56,060 --> 00:39:57,186
Just like you said, Jack.

539
00:40:00,189 --> 00:40:02,066
I have to face
the consequences of my choices.

540
00:40:21,627 --> 00:40:22,461
Sorry about that.

541
00:40:23,003 --> 00:40:24,422
My friend group can be a bit dramatic.

542
00:40:25,464 --> 00:40:27,049
We didn't even get to start the read-through.

543
00:40:27,466 --> 00:40:28,175
No worries.

544
00:40:29,051 --> 00:40:32,054
If I were Jack, I'd take a break too.

545
00:40:35,099 --> 00:40:37,017
Is Dean okay, though?

546
00:40:38,853 --> 00:40:39,895
I think he is now.

547
00:40:39,895 --> 00:40:41,105
I talked to him.

548
00:40:41,814 --> 00:40:43,274
He just wanted some time alone.

549
00:40:45,276 --> 00:40:45,776
Mm.

550
00:40:51,574 --> 00:40:52,366
That's good.

551
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:55,286
Now that I have some free time,
I'm going to be a TikToker.

552
00:40:56,871 --> 00:40:58,080
A TikToker?

553
00:41:04,503 --> 00:41:06,881
♪ Would you mind ♪

554
00:41:06,881 --> 00:41:09,175
♪ If I fell for you? ♪

555
00:41:14,472 --> 00:41:16,265
People who can dance are cool.

556
00:41:16,682 --> 00:41:20,811
Anyone can get good at it
with enough practice.

557
00:41:21,770 --> 00:41:22,938
Come. Practice with me.

558
00:41:23,564 --> 00:41:24,148
Come on.
Practice what?

559
00:41:24,773 --> 00:41:25,649
Dancing.

560
00:41:26,358 --> 00:41:27,359
Me? Dancing?

561
00:41:27,359 --> 00:41:28,277
Yes.

562
00:41:28,569 --> 00:41:29,487
Come on.

563
00:41:30,863 --> 00:41:32,448
♪ Would you mind ♪

564
00:41:34,074 --> 00:41:34,950
Wait.

565
00:41:36,076 --> 00:41:36,952
Start over.

566
00:41:36,952 --> 00:41:38,204
Okay. Let's start again.

567
00:41:39,163 --> 00:41:40,998
♪ Would you mind ♪

568
00:41:41,415 --> 00:41:43,250
♪ If I fell for you? ♪

569
00:41:45,669 --> 00:41:47,254
I'd rather sit and watch you.

570
00:41:51,342 --> 00:41:52,968
Let's pause for now.

571
00:41:58,432 --> 00:42:00,392
Tua, can I ask you something?

572
00:42:01,852 --> 00:42:03,687
What's up with you and Boston?

573
00:42:04,021 --> 00:42:05,105
You don't like him?

574
00:42:09,443 --> 00:42:10,528
Well…

575
00:42:12,488 --> 00:42:13,739
It's a long story.

576
00:42:13,906 --> 00:42:16,408
Oh please. I've got time.

577
00:42:18,452 --> 00:42:20,371
Unless you don't want to talk about it.

578
00:42:20,371 --> 00:42:21,664
Then I'll stop asking.

579
00:42:23,249 --> 00:42:28,963
I'm asking because
you seem uncomfortable around him.

580
00:42:30,089 --> 00:42:30,881
So what's the deal?

581
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:36,637
Do you remember
when I told you about my first kiss?

582
00:42:37,888 --> 00:42:38,305
Mm.

583
00:42:39,056 --> 00:42:39,682
It's him.

584
00:42:40,933 --> 00:42:41,809
My first kiss.

585
00:42:45,563 --> 00:42:47,565
But… It's…

586
00:42:50,025 --> 00:42:50,985
Why?

587
00:42:51,694 --> 00:42:52,861
You guys didn't end it well?

588
00:42:57,199 --> 00:43:00,411
I guess it's my fault for catching feelings.

589
00:43:01,620 --> 00:43:03,205
I wanted something more.

590
00:43:03,789 --> 00:43:06,000
But he ghosted me in every way possible.

591
00:43:07,960 --> 00:43:10,129
I guess he found someone new.

592
00:43:10,713 --> 00:43:13,716
It's shit luck we met again on this project.

593
00:43:14,883 --> 00:43:16,719
But I don't have
any feelings for him anymore.

594
00:43:17,678 --> 00:43:19,847
It's just… seeing him again
caught me off guard.

595
00:43:25,728 --> 00:43:29,732
Someone like Boston
doesn't deserve to be your first.

596
00:43:31,942 --> 00:43:34,361
He should be labeled as just your ex-enemy.

597
00:43:36,655 --> 00:43:37,990
That's true.

598
00:43:38,449 --> 00:43:39,575
How about this?

599
00:43:39,867 --> 00:43:44,496
Next time you see him
and feel uncomfortable, tell me.

600
00:43:45,164 --> 00:43:47,416
Give me a signal,
and I'll be your human shield.

601
00:43:49,710 --> 00:43:51,795
You're working as a bodyguard now?

602
00:43:52,796 --> 00:43:54,298
Sure. Of course, I am.

603
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:57,593
Tua.
Someone as lovely as you

604
00:43:58,469 --> 00:43:59,928
won't stay single for long.

605
00:44:04,183 --> 00:44:05,643
Okay?

606
00:44:06,060 --> 00:44:08,354
If you feel uncomfortable, let me know.

607
00:44:09,355 --> 00:44:10,356
Mm.

608
00:44:11,815 --> 00:44:13,942
If I'm not okay, I'll tell you.

609
00:44:44,932 --> 00:44:47,059
You fished that info out of Bas, didn't you?

610
00:44:49,728 --> 00:44:51,855
And you're the one
who leaked the news about Dean?

611
00:44:52,606 --> 00:44:53,732
I didn't do it.

612
00:44:54,900 --> 00:44:56,402
Who else could it be?

613
00:44:56,568 --> 00:44:59,988
After you followed me to that party,
the video got out.

614
00:45:00,572 --> 00:45:01,657
Isn't that too convenient?

615
00:45:01,657 --> 00:45:02,241
Hey.

616
00:45:03,158 --> 00:45:04,702
People who choose that kind of work

617
00:45:05,285 --> 00:45:09,748
should know their digital footprint
follows them for life.

618
00:45:13,210 --> 00:45:16,463
Besides, anyone could've done it.

619
00:45:19,299 --> 00:45:21,468
It's not just me who knows about it.

620
00:45:31,687 --> 00:45:34,815
How are you so sure it was me?

621
00:45:38,402 --> 00:45:39,069
Okay.

622
00:45:39,528 --> 00:45:41,321
Is this what you want?

623
00:45:42,865 --> 00:45:43,615
Fine.

624
00:45:44,158 --> 00:45:45,951
I've been a fool all this time.

625
00:45:47,119 --> 00:45:48,912
You won't get anything from me ever again.

626
00:45:50,289 --> 00:45:51,165
Are you done?

627
00:45:52,791 --> 00:45:54,084
I'm going to see Jack.

628
00:45:55,502 --> 00:45:57,379
I think he could use some comfort right now.

629
00:45:59,590 --> 00:46:01,467
There's no point in doing that.

630
00:46:06,930 --> 00:46:10,768
We'll see if I score some points doing that.

631
00:46:47,679 --> 00:46:48,972
Why are you here? Hm?

632
00:46:50,265 --> 00:46:51,809
I'm not in the mood to fight you.

633
00:46:52,351 --> 00:46:53,477
I'm not here to fight.

634
00:47:05,489 --> 00:47:11,036
I understand why
you did what you did back then.

635
00:47:14,540 --> 00:47:17,334
You wanted to ease your sister's burden.

636
00:47:17,334 --> 00:47:20,128
She worked every day to pay for your tuition.

637
00:47:21,755 --> 00:47:25,926
You wanted to be the one
who helped your family get out of debt.

638
00:47:32,641 --> 00:47:33,976
Dean.

639
00:47:35,561 --> 00:47:39,982
I don't mind at all that you used to be a host.

640
00:47:42,317 --> 00:47:46,947
If I chose you, it means
I accepted that part of you.

641
00:47:46,947 --> 00:47:52,953
If you really accepted it,
then why did you break up with me?

642
00:47:53,912 --> 00:47:56,373
Because it broke my heart that

643
00:47:57,124 --> 00:48:01,169
my boyfriend asked someone else for help
instead of coming to me first.

644
00:48:06,008 --> 00:48:07,759
Why, Dean?

645
00:48:07,759 --> 00:48:10,387
I think I'm capable of taking care of people.

646
00:48:10,762 --> 00:48:12,848
I never want to be a burden to anyone.

647
00:48:15,684 --> 00:48:21,064
People in love don't
see their partner as a burden.

648
00:48:42,544 --> 00:48:44,713
It's fine if you don't believe me,

649
00:48:44,713 --> 00:48:47,966
but I had nothing to do
with your secret coming out.

650
00:48:49,968 --> 00:48:55,098
No matter how angry I was,
I could never hurt you.

651
00:49:06,401 --> 00:49:08,654
Seeing you hurt…

652
00:49:12,449 --> 00:49:13,951
hurts me too.

653
00:49:21,458 --> 00:49:22,417
I'm fine.

654
00:49:22,459 --> 00:49:23,418
You're not.

655
00:49:24,461 --> 00:49:26,713
You're just pretending you are.

656
00:49:29,591 --> 00:49:32,427
Right now, you're here with me.

657
00:49:32,970 --> 00:49:35,847
You can feel whatever you need to feel.

658
00:49:36,390 --> 00:49:37,808
I won't judge you.

659
00:50:23,478 --> 00:50:25,272
I haven't seen this side of you in a long time.

660
00:50:27,566 --> 00:50:29,359
Let yourself be weak or lose sometimes.

661
00:50:30,736 --> 00:50:32,029
It won't kill you.

662
00:50:36,491 --> 00:50:38,452
I'm sorry…

663
00:50:41,455 --> 00:50:44,666
for being the reason you went to rehab.

664
00:50:49,796 --> 00:50:51,673
It's alright.

665
00:50:54,718 --> 00:50:57,721
I'm sorry too.

666
00:51:45,268 --> 00:51:46,686
(Next Episode)
Yes, I used to be James Dean.

667
00:51:46,686 --> 00:51:49,356
The VIP host you're gossiping about.

668
00:51:50,607 --> 00:51:53,068
You've got an ugly face
and an uglier personality, motherfucker!

669
00:51:53,235 --> 00:51:54,611
Boston DMed me.

670
00:51:54,903 --> 00:51:56,488
He asked me to model for a shoot at his studio.

671
00:51:56,988 --> 00:51:58,573
What exactly do you want, Boston?

672
00:51:59,866 --> 00:52:01,451
I want to go after you.

673
00:52:01,868 --> 00:52:03,453
Do you still love me?

674
00:52:03,620 --> 00:52:04,663
You got your answer.

675
00:52:04,663 --> 00:52:05,705
Jack is an idiot!

676
00:52:05,872 --> 00:52:07,082
He's back with that asshole Dean, damn it!

677
00:52:07,124 --> 00:52:08,041
Didn't I tell you?

678
00:52:08,208 --> 00:52:10,877
No matter how hard you tried,
he'd never want you.

